reviewText: Thank goodness for independent film making.  It allows our black artist the liberty to create and, produce and act in films that depict our stories.  This is a gritty piece but comes full circle.  It shows that although you may be in dire straits and situations, you do not have to be defined by them.  With discipline and determination you can push through and out of very bad conditions.  I suggest parents view this with teenagers and then have a discourse on making choices and the possible consequences of those choices.
Title: Cross to Bear, A
